abstract: One of Patrick Pizzella’s White House admirers calls him a “movement conservative” more likely than his predecessor to agree with the administration on cutting labor rules and weakening unions.
snippet: One of Patrick Pizzella’s White House admirers calls him a “movement conservative” more likely than his predecessor to agree with the administration on cutting labor rules and weakening unions.
lead_paragraph: Congressional Republicans, members of their staffs and conservative activists regularly flew first class to Saipan, an island just north of Guam in the Pacific Ocean. They slept at the beachfront Hyatt Regency, and dined on fresh Japanese cuisine.

abstract: Second-quarter totals show a lower tier of candidates burning through cash trying to stay viable, while the leaders banked millions. Who has more than 300 people on her payroll?
snippet: Second-quarter totals show a lower tier of candidates burning through cash trying to stay viable, while the leaders banked millions. Who has more than 300 people on her payroll?
lead_paragraph: Mayor Pete Buttigieg soared and Senator Elizabeth Warren surged. Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. was solid. Senator Bernie Sanders held steady. Senator Kamala Harris scored late.

abstract: While both candidates are firmly in the Democratic primary’s top tier, liberal activists aren’t convinced they are committed to widespread change.
snippet: While both candidates are firmly in the Democratic primary’s top tier, liberal activists aren’t convinced they are committed to widespread change.
lead_paragraph: WATERLOO, Iowa — Mayor Pete Buttigieg raised more money in the most recent quarter than anyone else in the 2020 field and has generated excitement among Democratic donors unseen for a new national political figure since Barack Obama’s first presidential campaign.

snippet: Mr. Biden, detailing his health care plan in Iowa, paraphrased a notorious promise made by Mr. Obama: “If you like your private insurance, you can keep it.”
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — It was the singular promise that doomed the public perception of President Barack Obama’s health care law — and now former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. is using it on the campaign trail.

abstract: In a race for a House seat, Ritchie Torres, a gay Bronx councilman, will oppose Rubén Díaz Sr., who says he doesn’t believe in gay marriage.
snippet: In a race for a House seat, Ritchie Torres, a gay Bronx councilman, will oppose Rubén Díaz Sr., who says he doesn’t believe in gay marriage.
lead_paragraph: In January, as Congress swore in a record 10 openly L.G.B.T.Q. members, Ritchie J. Torres, a 31-year-old Bronx councilman, recalled how the moment filled him with admiration, but also a sense that the accomplishment was still incomplete.
